utACK b1038af.

Nit, could get rid of `viewDummy` by using `viewChain` by default:
```cpp
        LOCK2(cs_main, mempool.cs);

        CCoinsViewCache& viewChain = *pcoinsTip;
        CCoinsViewMemPool viewMempool(&viewChain, mempool);
        CCoinsViewCache view(&viewChain);
        if (fCheckMemPool) {
            // switch cache backend to db+mempool in case user likes to query mempool
            view.SetBackend(viewMempool);
        }
```

But I wonder if it pays off dealing with both cases separately:
```cpp
if (fCheckMemPool) {
    LOCK2(cs_main, mempool.cs);
    CCoinsViewCache& viewChain = *pcoinsTip;
    CCoinsViewMemPool viewMempool(&viewChain, mempool);
    CCoinsViewCache view(&viewMempool);
    ...
} else {
    LOCK(cs_main);  // no need to lock mempool!
    CCoinsViewCache& viewChain = *pcoinsTip;
    CCoinsViewCache view(&viewChain);
    ...
}
```

@jnewbery The branch looks great :)
I will continue the development at https://github.com/romanz/bitcoin/commits/tidy_up_rest_test in the upcoming days.
Much appreciated, and thanks again!

